Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{16%oz} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and slice @button mushrooms{8%oz} into ¼-inch-thick pieces (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%oz}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, half the @fry seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, toss mushrooms with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, remaining @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, ¼ cup water (½ cup for 4 servings), and a pinch of @sugar{½%tsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low; stir in BBQ sauce mixture. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens and filling is coated, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Remove pan from heat.

While filling cooks, in a second medium bowl, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}, cilantro, lime zest, juice from half the lime (juice from whole lime for 4 servings), a drizzle of @olive oil{}, sugar, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Slice @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through. Toast until golden brown.

Fill toasted baguettes with BBQ mushroom mixture and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like (we highly recommend adding a bit of slaw to your sloppy joes too!).

Divide sloppy joes, potato wedges, and any remaining slaw between plates. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.